<subSubSection lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1678,2027]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese" box="[151,333,1678,1703]" firstAuthor="Berlese" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="242 - 271" refId="ref38994" refString="Berlese, A. (1910 a) Lista di nuove specie e nuovi generi di Acari. Redia, 6, 242 - 271." type="journal article" year="1910" yearSuffix="a">Berlese (1910a)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1910" box="[463,583,1678,1703]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Olopachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[463,583,1678,1703]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Olopachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[802,953,1678,1703]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[802,953,1678,1703]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in which the females have the anal and genitiventral shields fused together. 
<bibRefCitation author="Koroleva" box="[562,766,1714,1739]" firstAuthor="Koroleva" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="411 - 483" refId="ref42472" refString="Koroleva, E. V. (1977 b) Family Pachylaelaptidae Vitzthum, 1931. In: Ghilyarov, M. S. &amp; Bregetova, N. G. (Eds) Key to the Soil Inhabiting Mites. Mesostigmata, Nauka, Leningrad, pp. 411 - 483." type="book chapter" year="1977" yearSuffix="b">Koroleva (1977b)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Karg" box="[779,918,1714,1739]" firstAuthor="Karg" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 523" refId="ref42302" refString="Karg, W. (1993) Acari (Acarina), Milben. Parasitiformes (Anactinochaeta). Cohors Gamasina Leach. Raubmilben. 2. Uberarbeitete Auflage. Die Tierwelt Deutschlands, 59, 1 - 523." type="journal article" year="1993">Karg (1993)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Masan" box="[976,1146,1714,1739]" firstAuthor="Masan" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref43485" refString="Masan, P. (2007 a) A Review of the Family Pachylaelapidae in Slovakia, with Systematics and Ecology of European Species (Acari: Mesostigmata: Eviphidoidea). Institute of Zoology, Slovak Academy of Sciences, Bratislava, 247 pp." type="book" year="2007" yearSuffix="a">Mašán (2007a)</bibRefCitation>
considered this character state to be of generic importance because there is no other pachylaelapid genus with an entire genitiventrianal shield covering the posteroventral idiosoma. The genus was re-defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Masan" box="[1011,1176,1786,1811]" firstAuthor="Masan" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref43485" refString="Masan, P. (2007 a) A Review of the Family Pachylaelapidae in Slovakia, with Systematics and Ecology of European Species (Acari: Mesostigmata: Eviphidoidea). Institute of Zoology, Slovak Academy of Sciences, Bratislava, 247 pp." type="book" year="2007" yearSuffix="a">Mašán (2007a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Masan" box="[1189,1263,1786,1811]" firstAuthor="Masan" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="31 - 39" refId="ref43531" refString="Masan, P. (2007 b) Olopachys (Olopachylaella) gronychi subgen. nov., sp. nov., a new species of mite from Bulgaria (Acari: Mesostigmata: Pachylaelapidae). Zootaxa, 1509, 31 - 39." type="journal article" year="2007" yearSuffix="b">2007b</bibRefCitation>
), and currently comprises 14 described species distributed mainly throughout the Caucasus and adjacent regions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1678,2027]" lastBlockId="27.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1910" box="[231,351,1858,1883]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Olopachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[231,351,1858,1883]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Olopachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as in other genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1913" box="[603,788,1858,1883]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pachylaelapinae">Pachylaelapinae</taxonomicName>
, there are species with 1–2 spur-like distal setae on tarsus II, as well as species with dorsal setae J5 either minute or normal. 
<bibRefCitation author="Masan" box="[940,1114,1894,1919]" firstAuthor="Masan" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="31 - 39" refId="ref43531" refString="Masan, P. (2007 b) Olopachys (Olopachylaella) gronychi subgen. nov., sp. nov., a new species of mite from Bulgaria (Acari: Mesostigmata: Pachylaelapidae). Zootaxa, 1509, 31 - 39." type="journal article" year="2007" yearSuffix="b">Mašán (2007b)</bibRefCitation>
divided the genus into two subgenera, namely 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Masan" authorityYear="2007" box="[390,563,1930,1955]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Olopachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="26" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Olopachylaella">
<emphasis box="[390,563,1930,1955]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Olopachylaella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1910" box="[639,759,1930,1955]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Olopachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[639,759,1930,1955]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Olopachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[777,847,1931,1954]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Masan" authorityYear="2007" box="[1049,1222,1930,1955]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Olopachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Olopachylaella">
<emphasis box="[1049,1222,1930,1955]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Olopachylaella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be reliably distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1910" box="[370,490,1966,1991]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Olopachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[370,490,1966,1991]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Olopachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[497,556,1967,1990]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
mainly by the presence of normal needle-like clunal setae J5, and a shortened and foliate spermatodactyl. In general appearance, gnathosomal features and armature of legs II (not considering the fusion of the genitiventral shield and anal shield), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Masan" authorityYear="2007" box="[901,1074,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Olopachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Olopachylaella">
<emphasis box="[901,1074,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Olopachylaella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Masan" authorityYear="2007" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Longipachylaelaps">
<emphasis box="[1285,1436,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[160,373,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Longipachylaelaps</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
, which also has normally developed setae J5. More significant similarities in external morphology between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Masan" authorityYear="2007" box="[400,573,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Olopachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Olopachylaella">
<emphasis box="[400,573,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Olopachylaella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Masan" authorityYear="2007" box="[631,844,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="27" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Longipachylaelaps">
<emphasis box="[631,844,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Longipachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Masan" authorityYear="2007" box="[1014,1187,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Olopachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Olopachylaella">
<emphasis box="[1014,1187,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Olopachylaella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1910" box="[1246,1366,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Olopachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[1246,1366,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Olopachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1375,1436,224,247]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
suggest convergent or parallel evolution of the two 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1910" box="[747,867,260,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Olopachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[747,867,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Olopachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgenera as well as the secondary fusion of the genitiventral and anal shields in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Masan" authorityYear="2007" box="[514,686,295,320]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Olopachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Olopachylaella">
<emphasis box="[514,686,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Olopachylaella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
